tip.text: Good coffee from RoosLiberty, and great French toast. The savory breakfast dishes looked amazing so I'll definitely come back for that.

formattedAddress: 216 S State St (at E Liberty St)

tip.text: I don't say this lightly: amazing chicken fingers. Juicy, tender, very very fresh, the sauce goes with it perfectly.
Love the atmosphere here, somehow gives a San Francisco type of vibe. Breakfast was good. Get spicy scrambled eggs, if you like savory. The salted caramel French toast is TOO sweet for breakfast IMO.
Adorable and unique! Some items are very creepy though. I love that all of the older games are for about a quarter each, or 50 cents.
Quite possibly my favorite store in SF. So unique and anything here would make an amazing gift to people in your life that are interesting. I got a red fox tail that's so fluffy and soft.
Go solo if you want to be seated quickly without being wait listed. You can't go wrong with their rolls, my favorite is the Pokemon (mango!) and anything with eel.
The tres leches cake was gone in an instant from how fluffy and light it is.. But the real star is the banana cream tart. The BEST I've ever had. Flaky crust, flavorful filling, perfect texture.
Amazing coffee. So totally worth the hype. Get the New Orleans iced coffee if it was hot out, or the mocha if it was cold and you're craving hot chocolate.
I only had rolls here but they were all too wide to eat with chopsticks except Green Machine which happened to be the best roll there. The salmon cream cheese was delightful also.
The apple cider fritter is the best donut I have ever had. It's huge so it'll last you all day for nibbles!
Loved the latte. Made perfectly and the barista is very friendly.
Amazing huge bookstore. It seems as if it was tailored to my taste! GREAT SELECTION!
The only thing here I liked was the brisket, it was good. But everything else was mediocre at best and too salty. So much for best BBQ in Portland.
They are open till 3 AM. They sell hot slices of pizza. Sometimes there's nothing more you can ask!
I've stayed in a lot of fancy hotels, but this one is fancy AND cozy AND with a lot of character. On top of that, its location is perfect.
Had the breakfast egg sandwich, and the teriyaki meatball bahn mi, really filling, cheap and delicious. They bake their own bread and it suits their sandwiches.
I saved this place despite it being a bit far from downtown, just in case. We went to Museum of Flight and it was on our way back home. AMAZING BURGERS!!!!! Super flavorful. Super friendly.
I regret not getting the twice baked chocolate croissant, looked SO good! If you love lemony things, get the blueberry lemon dessert. It's delicious.

formattedAddress: 4737 California Ave SW (at SW Alaska St)

tip.text: The tat'strami. Get that one. It's the absolute best. I wish I lived in Seattle just for that sandwich. Changed my life and expectations of pastrami...
Amazing latte. I wouldn't come here for dessert, but yes... Get the latte. So good.
Nothing special, but it's good if you're nearby. Their espresso chocolate chip cookies with the dried apricots were nice. The cold brew coffee is also good.
The eggs were to die for in The Sonoran dish, killer hash browns and great waffles. Totally worth the 30 minute wait on a weekday.
I had the donuts with the heavenly vanilla bean mascarpone, and my husband had the golden brown pancakes. Both really delicious. Good atmosphere.
This place is kind of hidden, but the tacos are super delicious and very cheap. What's not to love?
Didn't have hope for this since it was located in a touristy area, but as a baker and a person who went to Paris: their almond croissant surpasses the ones in Paris. Amazing.
Not much here is memorable, except the sourdough bread which is amazing, and the lamb manicotti bechamel dish (don't know the exact name!)
Lamb shoulder is melt-in-your-mouth tender. It's soooooooo gooooooood.

formattedAddress: 45 Flinders Ln. (btwn Exhibition St. & Spring St.)

tip.text: The slow braised ribs and Mac and cheese were phenomenal.

formattedAddress: #01-05 Pan Pacific Serviced Suites (96 Somerset Rd.)

tip.text: Well worth the wait for brunch! Everything was perfect.
Why D.O.C. Pizza?
Not to be missed when you're in Melbourne. Best pizza I have ever had. The crust is amazing.
Loved the lamb and the apple pie. We started with the mushroom soup which was superb also!
Parmesan crusted chicken salad and the Butternut Asiago Tortellaci (picture posted) are my absolute favorites.
